Study Title: Clinical Study of UTD1 Injection in Combination With Capecitabine in Patients With Advanced and Metastatic Breast Cancer
Brief Summary: The purpose of this study is to determine whether UTD1 Injection in combination with capecitabine is effective in the treatment of advanced metastatic breast cancer using capecitabine as a control.
Interventions: DRUG: UTD1 Injection plus capecitabine|DRUG: Capecitabine
Secondary Outcome Measures: Overall survival (OS), 4 years|Objective Response Rate(ORRï¼‰, 1.5 years
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: NONE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
